channel.description: This is a randomly ordered feed of the most recent entries from INtopBackup, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Hamas fighters execute Palestinians they accuse of collaborating with Israel
item.description: Hamas is back on the streets of Gaza in an attempt, it says, to restore law and order -- and to send a message. Debora Patta reports.

item.title: Protesters clash with immigration agents in Chicago
item.description: Protesters in Chicago clashed with federal agents carrying out President Trump's immigration crackdown. Ash-har Quraishi has more.

item.description: But the president would not be drawn on whether the CIA had been told to topple Nicolas Maduro.

item.title: Senate fails to advance GOP funding bill for 9th time on Day 15 of shutdown
item.description: The government shutdown is in its third week as the Senate failed again to advance a House-passed measure to fund the government.

item.title: Trump says he authorized covert CIA operations in Venezuela
item.description: President Trump confirmed that he has authorized the CIA to go into Venezuela and conduct covert operations. Ed O'Keefe reports.

item.title: The federal government is still shut down. Here's what that means across the country
item.description: The federal government is currently shut down. The NPR Network is following the ways the government shutdown is affecting services across the country.
